leads.lead_text: At least some leaves more than trifoliolate
Terminal leaflet more or less sessile; leaflet margins entire
Terminal leaflet petiolulate and distant from lateral ones; leaflet margins toothed; north-west Victoria only
Petals twice as long as calyx; ovary glabrous; pod black, wrinkled
Petals slightly exceeding calyx; ovary and pod white-pubescent
Calyx 2–3 mm long, usually shorter than pod
Calyx 3.2–10 mm long, usually longer than pod
Plant a shrub with erect, much-branched stems, 0.5–2.5 m tall; inflorescence interrupted
Plant herbaceous with prostrate or ascending stems, usually less than 0.5 m tall; inflorescence continuous
Stems ascending then decumbent; corolla equal to or scarcely exceeding calyx
Stems usually prostrate; corolla exceeding calyx by c. 1 mm
Peduncle when in early flower mostly more than 26 mm long, more than 0.4 times the length of subtending leaf; corolla usually purple distally, white towards base
Peduncle when in early flower mostly less than 26 mm long, less than 0.4 times the length of subtending leaf; corolla usually white with a purplish blotch on keel
